From 27b99a0489cd22015edd2bd5d7b95b8d647c8be0 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Thiraviyam Mariyappan <tmariyap@qti.qualcomm.com>
Date: Sat, 28 Jun 2025 11:34:52 +0530
Subject: [PATCH 1/2] UPSTREAM:ath12k:DP: simplify rx buffer ring replenish
 logic

Currently, the rx buffer ring's spin_lock is taken before skb allocation
and dma mapping. This dma mapped buffer is attached to the buffer ring's
descriptor and ring's spin_unlock is performed. Since this lock is common
across the CPU cores, holding it during skb allocation and dma mapping
can be optimised.

Fix it by queuing the allocated skb in the rx_desc list without lock and
utilising this list during the ring replenishment helps to avoid
lock contention. Add counter in soc_dp_stats to track any excess buffer
getting allocated while following this simple replenishment path which
helps to ensure any excess buffer got allocated.

Additionally, dev_alloc_skb is used by CE and data path related rings.
Buffers allocated by data path rx goes via fast recycler to avoid clearing
few fields. When non data path rings allocates skb through the recycler,
the resultant skb may contains stale values. Fix it by calling
netdev_alloc_skb_fast instead dev_alloc_skb. netdev_alloc_skb_fast
internally performs skb recycler related functionality whereas
dev_alloc_skb follows traditional skb allocation flow.

patch-dependency:
0400-0001-UPSTREAM-DP-Use-paddr-from-rx_desc_info-instead-of-u.patch

Orginal patch:
955-02-ath12k-simplify-rx-buffer-ring-replenish-logic.patch
